We purchased the Thrifty bot encoders that connect to the analog port on the RoboRio. We have tried to use the YAGSL swerve drive starter code, however we are getting these errors on the CAN Bus.

image1216×255 135 KB

Any ideas on how we can fix this issue?

“talonfx” does not appear to be valid motor type; you want “falcon”. I’m not sure exactly what’s happening here, but it may be defaulting to Spark MAX NEOs if a valid motor type isn’t found (@nstrike?) (EDIT: I think is is slightly inaccurate, see note below)

Use the YAGSL config generator. It’ll ask you about everything you’re using, and you can click download at the end to get every .json in a zip. That should clean up any mistakes you may have made configuring it manually.

EDIT: Digging into the source, “talonfx” should be identical to specifying “krakenx60”, while an unrecognized motor would throw an error at runtime. So - “talonfx” still isn’t what you want, but that does not in fact explain why it’s trying to create Spark MAX NEOs; that suggests your config isn’t getting deployed properly.
